organic_results.title: Sibling resemblance and symmetry in intellectual skill
organic_results.snippet: This article uses data from High School and Beyond to examine the degree of sibling symmetry (the extent to which family background affects the intellectual ability of each sibling equally) and resemblance (the extent to which the intellectual skills of sibling pairs covary), paying particular attention to the roles of sex and ordinal position in modifying the degree of symmetry and resemblance. The results indicate considerable symmetry and little variation in resemblance in intellectual skill according to the sex and ordinal position of sibling pairs …
